Text.Value: Go ahead. We stand no chance against such forces. Let's end this together.
Behold, Duke Ravengard: the Absolute!
*Beneath the smoking ashes of Moonrise Towers, the elder brain lies destroyed. But what of the tadpoles it commanded?*
NO!
NO!
A rogue True Soul, flaunting it under your very nose. And you almost missed it.
You've built an army for our masters, true enough. But what of the Astral Prism?
It isn't you I answer to, Gortash.
*Freed of the Absolute's control, they will complete their transformations. A plague of illithids will soon descend on the Sword Coast, enslaving all they do not infect.*
Or the beginning of something else... You will not die today.
Trust me, Gale. We'll find another way.
The distractions have been yours, Ketheric. Perhaps we never should have dug your daughter up.
But I can't... This is it. I must do as Mystra commands.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: We fade to black and hear the sound of a huge explosion. We fade out and see a painting of Elminster looking over the distant ruins of Moonrise Towers, completely toppled. Mystra’s will was done, and the threat of the Absolute is over, but it cost our heroes their lives.

Text.Value: Now! It's really time we were going.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Gortash claps his hands, all energetic once more. He steps around the convulsing Ravengard and shoos at Ketheric, who steps back with a grimace.

Text.Value: *Freed of the Absolute's control, they will complete their transformations. A plague of illithids will soon descend on the Sword Coast, enslaving all they do not infect.*
Very well. Whether I condemn this world or not: I choose you.
You could choose me, the one who loves you. We can find another way together.
An elder brain... one of the cruellest and most powerful creatures in existence, enslaved by mere mortals.
An elder brain... one of the cruellest and most powerful creatures in existence, enslaved by mere mortals.
Please, Gale. It can't end like this. We can find another way. Together.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The light builds to a BLINDING AURA as  the brain shifts again, leaving only the marching army, nautiloids moving to follow.
EditorData.SFXTags: [EG] Plane shift leaving sound. Marching army foley.

Text.Value: To end it... To struggle on... It is a grave choice you're making for us both, but if it must be so - very well, I'll stand down to stand by you.
Shit, no - father!
*It is an ending, of sorts. Though not the one destiny had in store for you.*
*It is an ending, of sorts. Though not the one destiny had in store for you.*
We will empty this place and begin the march. You may catch up with the army once you've retrieved the weapon.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Tremors loosen stones from the rock wall as the brain pulls upwards
EditorData.SFXTags: [EG] Tremors/liquid sounds as the elder brain pulls upwards

Text.Value: Look at that crown. It radiates with power unlike anything I've ever seen. To have it... to hold... If only I could...
Orin and I can wait for you no longer. The plan proceeds - we're going to the city, and we expect you to follow - army and the weapon in tow.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Gortash turns to the face the brine pool, holding his gauntlet aloft, the gem inlaid in it glinting. Rolling her eyes, Orin raises her dagger, its gem glinting alike. The surface of the brine pool begins to bubble.

NO!
Oh, the General voice. Is this where we salute?
*There he is: the man who sold you to Zariel to live out your days in the Hells.*
There we are. It wouldn't do to fight in front of our guest.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The Brain extends a tentacle, and we follow it down to a slumped and bound Duke Ravengard.

Text.Value: Balthazar has them now. He'll deliver the Prism soon enough - so if you would cease these distractions, I -

Text.Value: You're right... we truly have no other choice. This is it, then - the end of ends.
And I am the hero who will save it.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Gortash gives a mocking wave as the tentacle reaches him, touching him, the glowing building - then grows BLINDING as the brain departs, plane-shifting Gortash, Ravengard and Orin with it. Still scowling, Ketheric turns away.

Text.Value: Shit, no - father!
Salute, yes, with cleavers through his blood-starved flesh. How it crawls with failure like flies on lick-wet carrion.
One last gust of Weave. One last gale to end them all.
*The orb senses your hesitation. It shudders within you - longing for something, though you cannot tell what.*
If the weapon is truly in your grasp, Ketheric, might I suggest closing your fist?

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Smirking, Gortash brings his hand up, a gauntlet shining on his fist.

Text.Value: It is time, faithful ones. March on Baldur's Gate. We go to prepare the way.

Text.Value: You wag your wordflap in vain, Ulderling. Once the worm holds the whip, your shredded flesh will serve us.

Text.Value: And Ketheric - do try not to sulk. You're supposed to be the fearsome General, come to conquer the city.

Text.Value: What choice do I have? More than just a goddess counts on my courage: whole worlds hang in the balance.
The slayer against the undying one. That would be fun to see.
*You realise that it could change everything. Your own course. Your own life. The destiny of worlds.*
*The sight of the crown atop the elder brain strikes you like lightning. Never before have you beheld an artefact of such unrivalled power.*
Stand down! This isn't your decision to make.
I do trust you. More than myself right now. Perhaps even more than Mystra.
Sure that they would follow, and deliver it into my hands here. If you would cease these distractions -
*Wyll freezes at the sight. His own father, Duke Ulder Ravengard, seized by the Chosen. Yet for now, there's little he can do.*
*Beneath the smoking ashes of Moonrise Towers, the elder brain lies destroyed. But what of the tadpoles it commanded?*
Obey your goddess. Detonate the orb. Destroy the Absolute.
*You freeze at the sight. Your own father, Duke Ulder Ravengard, seized by the Chosen. Yet for now, there's little you can do.*
*A prickling dread rises along your spine - you have disobeyed Mystra. Again. If you survive this, there will be consequences.*
His cryptbreath sings to my sinews, again again againagainagain!
You forget yourself, Orin. I have played my part.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: From the boiling surface of the brine pool, a MASSIVE SHAPE emerges. Tentacles writhing, the ELDER BRAIN hangs suspended. Gortash smiles - but then his face tightens in strain as the Brain TREMBLES, resisting.

Text.Value: It's one thing to sacrifice yourself, but you will not sacrifice your friends. You will wait - there will be another chance.

Synopsis: Upon entering the Ketheric boss chamber on the lower floor of the Colony, the party will see a cinematic of the Chosen Three gearing up to continue on to the next stage of their master plan. Ketheric, Orin and Gortash will be discussing the next steps and the tension caused by the player's actions. Ketheric tadpoles Duke Ravengard and we lay eyes upon the Elder Brain in the flesh. Orin and Gortash depart with the Duke and the Elder Brain in a nearby Nautiloid to march onto Baldur's Gate. We see the Nautiloid appear above Moonrise Towers and cue the armies of the Absolute to start marching. Ketheric stays behind to deal with some local issues.
